TH man 1 "19 JULY 2023" "0.1" "Simple Shell man page"

Simple Shell NAME
B Simple Shell
- Simple shell is crated in C Language to interrelate with a linux OS.

Simple Shell SYNOPSIS
 hsh [options] [file]

Simple Shell  DESCRIPTION
Shell is a UNIX term for the interactive user interface with an OS. The shell is the layer of programming that understands
and executes the commands a user enters. In some systems, the shell is called a command interpreter. A shell usually implies an interface
with a command syntax 

B Overview

The simple shell is a command that reads lines from either a file or the terminal, interprets them, and generally implements other commands. It is the program that is started when a user logs into the system. It incorporates many features to aid interactive use and has the advantage that the interpretative language is common to both interactive and non-interactive use (shell scripts). That is, commands can be typed directly to the running simple shell or can be put into a file, which can be executed directly by the simple shell.
Simple Shell Return Value

Always 0 for success, other number means failure.

Simple Shell PATH

It will look inside all the directions in PATH env variable for executable.

Simple Shell

Simple Shell OPTIONS
B simple shell
Command options will be typed after the main command followed by a space and a
 '-' symbol.

Simple Shell EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

Simple Shell BUGS
Single space required after argument.


